Gazprom Jumps as CFO Says Ebitda Expected to Rise 25 Percent

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-06-29T15:26:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/gazprom-jumps-after-cfo-says-ebitda-expected-to-rise-25-percent.html
OAO Gazprom, the Russian natural gas
export monopoly, gained to its highest in a week after Chief
Financial Officer Andrey Kruglov said adjusted earnings before
interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization are forecast to
increase 25 percent this year.  The stock rallied 1.4 percent to 201.46 rubles by the 6:45
p.m. close in Moscow.  Adjusted net income to Russian accounting standards may
reach 750 billion rubles ($27 billion) this year, Kruglov told
reporters today in Moscow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran at 
